abstract.2: born near rosetown, saskatchewan<University_of_Saskatchewan>, walter h. farquharson<Walter_H._Farquharson> was educated at the university of saskatchewan<University_of_Saskatchewan> (ba, 1957) and st andrew's college in the university of saskatchewan<University_of_Saskatchewan> (bd, 1961)

abstract.5: walter h. farquharson<Walter_H._Farquharson> is a noted hymn-writer; three of his hymns were published in the hymn book (anglican and united churches<United_Church_of_Canada> of canada, 1971); one of his best-known, "men go to god when they are sorely placed," a translation of dietrich bonhoeffer's menschen gehen zu gott in ihrer nott, also appeared in the australian hymn book (anglican, methodist, presbyterian, congregational and roman catholic)
